OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,FThe headline figure is that 2023 was
OL,8,Fthe second hottest year on record for
OL,9,Fthe UK as a whole, and the hottest
OL,10,Fever for Wales and Northern Ireland.
OL,12,FThe annual UK temperature was 1.66C
OL,13,Fhigher than the average between 1961
OL,14,Fand 1990.
OL,16,FThe report flagged two key trends. The
OL,17,Fnumber of "hot" days (28C or above)
OL,18,Fand "extremely wet" days are both
OL,19,Fincreasing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
