OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,FBetween 1961 and 1990, London and
OL,8,FHampshire were the only places to
OL,9,Faverage six or more days over 28C.
OL,11,FBut in 2023, that rose to 20 days
OL,12,Facross 11 different counties in the
OL,13,Fsouth and east of England.
OL,15,FThe number of "extremely wet" days was
OL,16,F20% higher in the most recent decade
OL,17,Fthan in the 60s, 70s and 80s.
