OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,FProfessor Liz Bentley, Chief Executive
OL,8,Fof the Royal Meteorological Society
OL,9,Fsaid: "The new analysis of days that
OL,10,Fare classified as 'hot' or having
OL,11,F'exceptional rainfall' highlights the
OL,12,Fincreased frequency in high impact
OL,13,Fextremes we are already experiencing
OL,14,Fin the UK.
OL,16,F"The attribution studies help to
OL,17,Funderstand how human activities, such
OL,18,Fas burning fossil fuels, are making
OL,19,Fthese extreme events much more likely
OL,20,Fto happen as our climate continues to
OL,21,Fchange."
