OL,3,CMet Office warns of rise in extreme UK
OL,4,Cweather, as 2023 second hottest year
OL,5,Cever
OL,7,FForecasters say the frequency of these
OL,8,Fextremes will put added pressure on
OL,9,Fhealth services and infrastructure.
OL,10,FWhat's more, they say last year's
OL,11,Fextremes will become the new norm.
OL,13,F"By 2050, a year like 2023 would be
OL,14,Ffairly average, and by the end of the
OL,15,Fcentury, it is likely to be a very
OL,16,Fcool year," lead author and Met Office
OL,17,Fclimate scientist Mike Kendon said.
OL,19,F"These projections going forward show
OL,20,Fus just how dramatically we expect our
OL,21,Fclimate to change in the future."
